@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About - Contoso Risk Analysis Platform</PageTitle>

<div class="info-page">
    <div class="info-container">
        <h1>About Contoso Risk Analysis Platform</h1>
        
        <div class="info-section">
            <p class="lead">
                The Contoso Risk Analysis Platform (CRAP) is an innovative AI-powered solution that demonstrates 
                the seamless integration of Microsoft Azure AI and Elasticsearch for intelligent risk assessment 
                and document analysis.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>
                This platform showcases modern cloud architecture patterns, combining Azure's powerful AI services 
                with Elasticsearch's advanced search and analytics capabilities. Built with .NET 9 and Blazor WebAssembly, 
                it provides a fast, responsive user experience for risk analysis workflows.
            </p>
            <p>
                The solution processes PDF documents, extracts relevant information, and uses AI agents to provide 
                intelligent insights about risk factors, compliance requirements, and business impacts.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>Azure AI Foundry:</strong> Powers the intelligent agent with GPT-4 models</li>
                <li><strong>Elasticsearch:</strong> Provides fast, semantic search across document repositories</li>
                <li><strong>Azure Functions:</strong> Serverless backend for document processing and API endpoints</li>
                <li><strong>Blazor WebAssembly:</strong> Modern, responsive web interface</li>
                <li><strong>Microsoft Teams Integration:</strong> Native bot for risk assessment queries</li>
                <li><strong>Azure Content Safety:</strong> Ensures responsible AI with content moderation</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Built for ElasticON 2025</h2>
            <p>
                This project was created by <a href="https://aka.ms/mrichter" target="_blank">Mike Richter</a> to 
                demonstrate best practices for integrating Microsoft Azure and Elasticsearch at ElasticON 2025. 
                It serves as a reference implementation for organizations looking to build AI-powered document 
                analysis and risk assessment solutions.
            </p>
            <p>
                The complete source code and documentation are available on 
                <a href="https://github.com/michaelsrichter/azure-elastic-risk-agent" target="_blank">GitHub</a>, 
                allowing developers to explore, learn from, and adapt the solution for their own use cases.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Open Source & Community</h2>
            <p>
                This is a demonstration project showcasing the power of combining Azure AI and Elasticsearch. 
                We encourage the community to explore the codebase, provide feedback, and use it as a starting 
                point for their own risk assessment and document analysis solutions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-section">
            <a href="https://github.com/michaelsrichter/azure-elastic-risk-agent" target="_blank" class="cta-button">
                View on GitHub
            </a>
            <a href="/" class="cta-button secondary">
                Try the Platform
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
